# Forms & shadcn UI

## Shared hook (`hooks/use-app-form.tsx`)

Use `useAppForm` + `useTypedAppFormContext` from `createFormHook` — not ad-hoc form context.

## Multi-section forms

1. Zod schema + `defaultValues` + `formOptions({ defaultValues })`.
2. Parent: `useAppForm({ ...formOptions, validators: { onSubmit: schema }, onSubmit })`.
3. Wrap children in `<form.AppForm>`.
4. Children: `useTypedAppFormContext(formOptions)` (same options for types).
5. Slice state: `useStore(form.store, (s) => s.values.text)`.

## Field + shadcn

```tsx
<form.Field name="name">
  {(field) => {
    const isInvalid = field.state.meta.isTouched && !field.state.meta.isValid;
    return (
      <Field data-invalid={isInvalid}>
        <Input value={field.state.value} onChange={(e) => field.handleChange(e.target.value)} onBlur={field.handleBlur} aria-invalid={isInvalid} />
        {isInvalid && <FieldError errors={field.state.meta.errors} />}
      </Field>
    );
  }}
</form.Field>
```

## UI composition

- Prefer shadcn (`components/ui/*`) first: Button, Input, Field, Select, Dialog, etc.
- Build feature/custom components by composing shadcn — do not reinvent primitives.
- Mutations: `useMutation(trpc....mutationOptions({}))`; toast + invalidate on success.
